  • Method Details

    • newInstance

      public static JsonSink newInstance(RepeatedByte output)
      Create a new JsonSink that writes directly to the given output. If more bytes are written than fit in the array, the size will grow as needed.

      Note that growing is quite inefficient, so the buffers should have an appropriate initial size and be reused.

    • newInstance

      public static JsonSink newInstance()
      Create a new JsonSink with a new internal buffer. The size of the buffer will grow as needed. The resulting buffer can be accessed with getBytes()

      The output is minimized JSON without extra whitespace for sending data over the wire. Enums are serialized as strings by default.

    • newPrettyInstance

      public static JsonSink newPrettyInstance()
      Create a new JsonSink with a new internal buffer. The size of the buffer will grow as needed. The resulting buffer can be accessed with getBytes()

      The output contains extra whitespace to improve human readability

    • setOutput

      public JsonSink setOutput(RepeatedByte output)
      Changes the output to the given bytes. This resets any existing internal state and is equivalent to creating a new instance.

    • setWriteEnumsAsInts

      public JsonSink setWriteEnumsAsInts(boolean writeEnumsAsInts)
      Serializes enum values as JSON integers rather than human- readable strings. Compatible parsers are able to parse either case.

      Unknown values will still be serialized as numbers.

      Parameters:
      writeEnumsAsInts - true if values should use strings
      Returns:
      this

    • setPreserveProtoFieldNames

      public JsonSink setPreserveProtoFieldNames(boolean preserveProtoFieldNames)
      The serialized JSON object keys map to the value defined by the 'json_name' option, or the lowerCamelCase version of the field name in the proto file.

      This option lets users choose to preserve the original field names as defined in the proto file. Conforming parsers accept both keys.

      Parameters:
      preserveProtoFieldNames - true uses the original field names as JSON object keys
      Returns:
      this

    • setPrettyPrinting

      public JsonSink setPrettyPrinting(boolean prettyPrinting)
      Sets the output to be pretty printed (newlines and spaces) for increased readability, or minified (default without whitespace) for efficiency.
      Parameters:
      prettyPrinting - true adds whitespace to make the result more human-readable
      Returns:
      this
